    <section id="id16327290">
      <title>Electronegativity</title>
      <para id="id16327310">The electronegativities of silicon and carbon are given in Table along with hydrogen. Since carbon is more electronegative than hydrogen the C-H bond is polarized towards carbon resulting in a more protic hydrogen (<link target-id="id16327460"/>a). In contrast, the lower electronegativity of silicon results in a more hydridic hydrogen (<link target-id="id16327460"/>b). This difference is reflected in the reaction chemistry of SiH<sub>4</sub> versus CH<sub>4</sub>. </para>


